description.narrative: UNICEF's voice and public engagement significantly enhanced, particularly with GRN and key partners, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Private Sector Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2023, government institutions at the national and regional level are routinely reporting on the realization of the rights of all children and adolescents .

description.narrative: UNICEF Namibia continued to redefine its role in the country and repositioned itself in relation to upstream advocacy to leverage resources for children and influence decisions that will positively impact on the rights of children and women in the country. With this repositioning, UNICEF sought to incorporate innovative strategies through Social Policy engagements, Public Private Partnerships and youth participation. This has enabled the CO to increase focus on and advocate for child-related national policies and programmes that directly benefit all children especially those living in hard to reach areas. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
